The paper deals with the problem of multi-label classification using binary classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method involves a probabilistic model and a soft confusion matrix, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE).
